  <!-- Body -->
  <div style="padding:3rem 0 7rem;">
    <div class="max-w-[780px] mx-auto px-8" style="font-size:0.97rem;color:var(--color-text-secondary);line-height:1.9;display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:1.75rem;">

      <p>Nundah sits about eight kilometres north of the CBD with direct rail connections via Nundah Station on both the Doomben and Airport lines. It borders Clayfield and Ascot to the south, which has historically created a consistent spillover buyer dynamic: families and professionals who have been priced out of those suburbs, or who are looking for comparable character at a lower entry point, find Nundah's residential streets an intentional landing place rather than a compromise. The Sandgate Road commercial strip anchors the suburb's commercial life, while the quieter residential streets behind it deliver the low-density character that owner-occupiers are paying for.</p>

      <p>The suburb is genuinely two zones operating under one name. The properties along and near Sandgate Road, and in the concentrated apartment and unit layer around the station precinct, are measured against a different comparable set and attract a different buyer than the character homes in the residential streets further from the commercial centre. Understanding which zone your property sits in, and which buyer it is designed to reach, is the first decision a Nundah campaign has to make correctly.</p>

      <h2 style="font-family:var(--font-serif);font-size:1.5rem;font-weight:400;color:var(--color-text-primary);">Who is buying in Nundah</h2>
      <p>The character home buyer in Nundah is typically someone who has done the research on the inner north corridor and understands the price relationship between Clayfield, Ascot and Nundah. They are not arriving at Nundah by accident. They have identified that the character streetscape in the residential areas is genuine, that the rail access is exceptional, and that the price gap relative to their first-preference suburbs gives them significantly more home for their budget. When a well-presented Queenslander or workers cottage in the right Nundah street comes to market at a defensible price, this buyer moves quickly.</p>

      <p>The investor buyer is a significant second segment. Nundah's rail access to the CBD and the airport creates strong professional rental demand that investors understand and price into their acquisition decisions. This buyer is largely yield and vacancy-driven rather than emotional, which means the campaign needs to present financial as well as lifestyle credentials to reach them effectively.</p>

      <h2 style="font-family:var(--font-serif);font-size:1.5rem;font-weight:400;color:var(--color-text-primary);">What drives value in Nundah</h2>
      <p>In the character home segment, street position relative to the Sandgate Road corridor is the primary variable. A property in a quiet, tree-lined residential street away from the commercial strip will trade at a meaningful premium over a comparably sized property on a busier road or immediately adjacent to the commercial precinct. Character retention is the secondary driver: buyers who seek out Nundah's character homes are making that choice deliberately, and a home where original features have been stripped in favour of a generic renovation loses the audience it was meant to attract.</p>

      <p>In the apartment and unit segment, building quality, body corporate history and proximity to the station precinct are the primary factors. Investors look at sinking fund balances, levy schedules and recent maintenance records before committing. Having this documentation ready at the start of a campaign signals professionalism and removes a common friction point from the negotiation process.</p>

      <h2 style="font-family:var(--font-serif);font-size:1.5rem;font-weight:400;color:var(--color-text-primary);">Preparing your Nundah property for sale</h2>
      <p>For character homes, the exterior presentation is the campaign's opening statement. The Nundah character home buyer is searching specifically for this type of property in these streets, and the first photograph has to confirm immediately that this is what they have been looking for. A maintained facade, tidy garden and clean pathways communicate that the property has been cared for. Inside, the goal is clean, well-lit photography that showcases original features without imposing a contemporary style layer that conflicts with the period character.</p>

      <p>For apartments and units, the key preparation investment is documentation. A complete disclosure package that includes body corporate records, levy schedules, sinking fund balances and any known upcoming maintenance lets buyers conduct their due diligence without delay. Investors in this market segment are experienced and thorough. Having everything ready from day one shortens the path to unconditional contracts.</p>

      <h2 style="font-family:var(--font-serif);font-size:1.5rem;font-weight:400;color:var(--color-text-primary);">Best time to sell in Nundah</h2>
      <p>Nundah's mixed buyer profile, combining owner-occupiers and investors, gives it a more consistent year-round demand curve than purely family-driven markets. Investors respond to financial fundamentals rather than school enrolment calendars, which means demand does not drop as sharply in the winter months as it does in suburbs where school catchment timing dominates. That said, the two strongest windows for the character home market specifically are autumn (March to May) and spring (September to November). A Nundah campaign launched in either of these windows with the right preparation and positioning will find genuine competition from both buyer segments.</p>

      <h2 style="font-family:var(--font-serif);font-size:1.5rem;font-weight:400;color:var(--color-text-primary);">How long does it take to sell in Nundah</h2>
      <p>Well-presented Nundah character homes in the residential streets typically go under contract within 28 to 42 days when the pricing is grounded in recent comparable evidence. The investor-driven apartment market tracks slightly longer at 35 to 55 days, depending on the specific building, floor plan configuration and asking price relative to current comparable sales. In both segments, an honest price from the outset is what separates a clean campaign from one that stalls and eventually has to reduce to find its buyer. Properties that are correctly positioned and well-presented at launch attract competition. Properties that are overpriced sit and become associated with a narrative that is hard to reverse.</p>

